$lang['Hexadecimal numbers are made up of 16 digits instead of the 10 in a decimal number. The order of these numbers starts over after F (or 15 in decimal), while it doesn’t in the decimals. Check out the table below to see how they compare!'] = 'Dinomoro tša heksadesimale di bopilwe ka dinomoro tše 16 go e na le tše 10 ka palo ya tesimale. Tatelano ya dinomoro tše e thoma lefsa ka morago ga F (goba 15 ka tesimale), mola e sa dire bjalo ka ditesimale. Lekola tafola ye e lego ka mo tlase go bona gore di bapetša bjang!';
