$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Ka mohlala, ge motho a nyaka go fetolela 9F7A go tesimale, o be a tla thoma ka go arola 9F7A ka 16 yeo e lekanago le 6051. Ke moka o be a tla arola dinomoro tše dingwe le tše dingwe tša 6051 ka 16 yeo e lekanago le 381. Mafelelong, o be a tla oketša 381 + 381 + 381 yeo e lekanago 1144. Ka fao, 9F7A ka tesimale e lekana le 1144';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'O fetolela bjang Decimal go Hexadecimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Go fetolela tesimale go heksadesimale ke tshepedišo ye bonolo, gomme e ka dirwa ka sebaleledi goba sefetoledi sa inthanete. Gore o kgone go fetolela palo, e arole ka 16 gomme o tšee mašaledi. Mašaledi a ka morago a tla sepelelana le dinomoro tša heksadesimale. Mohlala, ge o na le nomoro ya tesimale 234, e arole ka 16 gomme o tšee mašaledi: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Ka fao, ka tšhupamabaka ya heksadesimale, palo ye e be e tla ngwalwa bjalo ka “E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Go na le didirišwa tše ntši tšeo di hwetšagalago inthaneteng tšeo di ka thušago ka go fetolela magareng ga dinomoro tša tesimale le tša heksadesimale. Go oketša moo, bontši bja di- calculator di na le mošomo wo o ageleditšwego ka gare wo o tlago go go dumelela go dira phetošo ye gabonolo kudu. Ka go klika ga mmalwa feela ga toeba goba go kgotla khiiboto, o tla kgona go fetoša boleng le ge e le bofe bja tesimale go ba bjo bo lekanago le bjona bja heksadesimale bjo bo swanetšego!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Ke mehola efe ya go šomiša Hexadecimal go feta Decimal?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'Tshepedišo ya hexadecimal goba base-16 e be e hlametšwe go ekiša tše dingwe tša dithoto tše di swanago le tša tshepedišo ya tesimale. Ka mantšu a mangwe, e bopilwe go nolofatša dilo go rena batho. Palo ya 423 e na le dinomoro tše 16 go e na le dinomoro tše 10 tšeo di hwetšagalago ka tshepedišong ya tesimale. Se ke ka lebaka la gore hexadecimal e šomiša motheo wa maswao a 16 go e na le 10. Ka morago ga F, tatelano e thoma gape ka 0 bjalobjalo bjalobjalo go fihlela re fihla go 15 yeo e ngwadilwego bjalo ka F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Go ngwala khoutu ya hexadecimal go fokotša palo ya dinomoro ka lebaka la seswai ge go bapetšwa le tshepedišo ya tesimale. Go oketša moo, dinomoro tša heksadesimale di na le segokanyipalo sa tshedimošo seo se phagamego gabedi go feta dinomoro tša tesimale. Ka gona, ke ka baka la’ng o swanetše go itshwenya ka go ithuta lenaneo le le lenyenyane la dinomoro la funky? Ka gobane e ka dira gore bophelo bja gago bo be bonolo! Ge o šoma ka ditshepedišo tša dijithale goba phetišetšo ya data, go šomiša hex go tla go bolokela nako le maatla ge o hlatholla melaetša ya sephiri goba melapo ya data.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ke mehola efe ya go šomiša Tesimale go feta Heksadesimale?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Ge go tliwa go go ngwala dikhoutu tša binary, Hexadecimal e šoma gabotse kudu ka gobane e fokotša dinomoro tše 8 go fihla go 2. Go tlaleletša, Hex e fa tekanyo ye kgolo ya segokanyipalo sa tshedimošo le go nepagala mo go phagamego ka dipalo go feta ka fao binary e dirago ka gona. Se se hlolwa ke taba ya gore Hex e šomiša maswao a 16 go e na le a mabedi fela go swana le binary. Ka lebaka la bokgoni bjo bjo bo oketšegilego, Hexadecimal gantši e šomišwa ge go ngwala dikhoutu tša binary ka go dikhomphutha le elektroniki ya dijithale gammogo le bakeng sa dikgopelo tša saense ya khomphutha.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Go tlaleletša, Hexadecimal e tšea sekgoba se senyenyane go feta tesimale. Ka dinomoro tše pedi fela go e na le dinomoro tše 8 tša binary, dinomoro tša Hex di emela dinomoro tše kgolo ka boripana kudu. Se se ka thuša kudu ge o šoma ka ditshepedišo tša khomphutha, ka ge go na le sebaka se senyenyane sa diphošo ge o thaepa dikhoutu tša hex ge di bapetšwa le dikhoutu tša tesimale tšeo di nago le dintlha tše ntši kudu tša tesimale lefelong ka moka!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Ke mohuta ofe wa dikelo tšeo di ka emelwago ke Hexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Nomoro ya heksadesimale ke nomoro yeo e šomišago dinomoro tše 16 go e na le dinomoro tše 10 tšeo re di šomišago mo tshepedišong ya tesimale. Tshepedišo ye ya dinomoro e bitšwa motheo-16, gomme e re thuša go ekiša dithoto tša tshepedišo ya rena ya tesimale yeo re e tlwaetšego. Ka hexadecimal, nomoro ye nngwe le ye nngwe e emela maatla a 16. Dinomoro tša 0 go ya go 9 di emela maatla a 1 go ya go 10, mola A go ya go F e emela maatla a 11 go ya go 15.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Go swana le ka tesimale, ka morago ga ge maswao a 16 a šomišitšwe ka go Hexadecimal, tatelano ya dinomoro e thoma gape go lefela. Ka fao, heksadesimale 10 e lekana le tesimale 16, gomme heksadesimale 11 e lekana le tesimale 17. Jwalo bjalo!';
