$lang['Hexadecimal is a way of representing binary data in human-readable form. It was developed in the 19th century to allow computers to store large amounts of information.'] = 'Hexadecimal ke tsela ya go emela ya data binary ka mokgwa wa go balwa ke motho. E hlamilwe lekgolong la bo-19 la nywaga bakeng sa go dumelela di- computer go boloka tsebišo e ntši.';
$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'O ka šomiša heksadesimale go fetolela magareng ga boleng bja tesimale le bja binary. Mohlala, go fetolela 10011011001010 go hexadecimal go be go tla feletša ka 0x4F. Se se ra gore boleng bja 4F bo emela nomoro ya binary 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Dipalo le saenseng ya khomphutha, hexadecimal (gape motheo wa 16, goba hex) ke tshepedišo ya dipalo ya maemo yeo e nago le radix, goba motheo, wa 16. E šomiša maswao a lesometshela a go fapana, gantši maswao a 0–9 go emela dikelo tša lefela go ya go tše senyane, . le A, B, C, D, E, F (goba ka tsela ye nngwe a–f) go emela dikelo tše lesome go ya go tše lesomehlano. Ka mohlala, palo ya heksadesimale 2AF3 e lekana, ka tesimale, le (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , kapa 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Nomoro ye nngwe le ye nngwe ya hexadecimal e emela dinomoro tše nne tša binary (bits) (tšeo gape di bitšwago &quot;nibble&quot;), gomme tšhomišo ya mathomo ya notation ya hexadecimal ke bjalo ka boemedi bjo bo nago le bogwera bja batho bja dikelo tša khoutu ya binary ka go dikhomphutha le elektroniki ya dijithale. Go fa mohlala, dikelo tša baete di ka tloga go 0 go ya go 255 (tesimale) eupša di ka emelwa gabonolo bjalo ka dinomoro tše pedi tša heksadesimale mo lefelong la 00 go ya go FF. Hexadecimal e šomišwa gape ka tlwaelo go emela diaterese tša memori ya khomphutha.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ke khutsofatšo ya Hexadecimal, yeo e theilwego godimo ga sebopego sa motheo -16 gomme e šomišwa go nolofatša ka fao ditaelo go dikhomphutha di emetšwego ka gona. Tshepedišo ye ya dinomoro tša maswao a 16 e hlamilwe bjalo ka mokgwa wa go thibela nomoro ya binary ya 8-bit, ka fao ya data e ka ngwalwa ka khoutu ka dikhomphutha ntle le maiteko. E ka gatišwa le go thaepa ka go šomiša dinomoro tše pedi tša hex tše di fapanego ka dinomoro tše dingwe le tše dingwe tša hex tšeo di bontšhago nibble goba mohlomongwe sebopego sa 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Tshepedišo ye ya dinomoro e šomiša maswao a 16 ao a emetšwego ka tekanyo ya go tloga go 0-9 goba AF. Di-0–9 di emela dinomoro go fihla go tše senyane mola AF e emetšwe ke dipalo tša 10–15. Ge go bapetšwa le mehuta ye mengwe ye meraro ya ditshepedišo tša dipalo, tshepedišo ya dipalo ya heksadesimale e tšewa e le yeo e šomago kudu.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Khoutu ya gago ya hexadecimal ga e šome';
